The '''Ashern''' (Vratix for "Black Claw") were members of the [[Vratix/Legends|Vratix]] race who had become disenchanted with the [[Human/Legends|Human]] control of the [[Bacta/Legends|bacta]] cartels on [[Thyferra/Legends|Thyferra]]. To fight against them, they resorted to drastic acts such as terrorism (uncommon for such a peaceful race) and even underwent modifications such as sharpening their claws and painting their carapaces black.

==History==
In [[7 BBY/Legends|7 BBY]] the Ashern decided to give out information showing that the [[Xucphra Corporation]] augmented the prices of bacta during the [[Stark Hyperspace War/Legends|Stark Hyperspace War]] by sabotaging production, and this ceded governmental control of the planet to the Vratix, leading to the [[Alazhixazha|Thriving Season]].<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref>

Through [[Qlaern Hirf]], the Ashern approached [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]] and declared their intentions to join the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]]. Other Ashern assisted [[Iella Wessiri Antilles|Iella Wessiri]], [[Elscol Loro]] and [[Sixtus Quin]] in their undercover attempts to overthrow [[Ysanne Isard]]. A group of Ashern commandos fought against Isard's regime, taking part in successful operations against [[Aerin Dlarit]] in his [[Dlarit estate|estate]] and the assault on the [[Xucphra Corporate Headquarters]].

